A chairde,

T=E1 s=FAil agam go bhfuil sibh go maith!

Our 'Seanfhocal' for this week was: 'is fearr cara sa ch=FAirt n=E1 punt sa=
spar=E1n'
Literal translation =3D A friend in court is better than a pound in the pur=
se
Meaning =3D This seanfhocal has 2 meanings. 1. It means having well-connect=
ed friends or influence in high places is more valuable than having money, =
especially in times of trouble or
2. It's more important to have friends (on your side) then to have wealth (=
in a more wholesome context).

Last night:

  *
We completed page 62, reading about Viktor Bocht (Poor Viktor) and we compl=
eted the questions Ceacht 14.0 in pairs.
  *
Having read about Viktor we were introduced to the verb 'Bh=ED' which is th=
e past tense of the irregular verb 'b=ED - to be.
  *
We went through page 63 as we began learning a new tense 'An Aimsir Chaite'=
 (the past tense)
  *
We then went through the attached PowerPoint learning the rules for the pas=
t tense
  *
The past tense is also covered in the textbook from pages 76-84 so feel fre=
e to go through those pages also!
  *
We completed Ceacht 19.0 on pg. 80 and I suggested reading about Gear=F3id =
Br=F3nach and completing Ceacht 19.1 as practice at home!


  *
I have also attached a PDF 'An Aimsir Chaite - Achoimre' that may be helpfu=
l and easier to follow than the powerpoint and textbook for some people!
  *
Here is a link to a video explaining the Aimsir Chaite that some people may=
 find useful! - https://rangmaher.com/rang-gaeilge-aimsir-chaite-2/

Remaining Class Dates:


  1.
Monday 30th of March =96 Extra Class 7-9pm (Rescheduled from the 16/03)
  2.
1 more class to be made up from the 09/03 - the following Monday (6th of Ap=
ril) is a Bank Holiday so we can do the following Monday (13th of April) or=
 else I can do Tuesday the 7th or Wednesday 8thof April at the usual time, =
if people didn't want to wait another week! I will put a poll in the WhatsA=
pp Groupchat!

Go raibh m=EDle maith agaibh agus b=EDodh seachtain deas agaibh!

Le gach dea-ghu=ED,

Laoise Nic =CDomhair

Oifigeach Forbartha Gaeilge, Barr na gCnoc

Ionad na Gaeilge Labhartha  | Col=E1iste na hOllscoile Corcaigh | Corcaigh =
| =C9ire
